# Mercury Architecture

For full structure and key files, see [mercury-fork/CLAUDE.md](mercury-fork/CLAUDE.md). Do not duplicate that content here.

## Key Directories

| Dir | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| `core/` | Runtime, handler, router, API routes, permissions, trigger |
| `agent/` | Docker container spawn, container-entry (calls pi) |
| `extensions/` | Loader, hooks, jobs, config-registry, skills, image-builder |
| `bridges/` | PlatformBridge implementations (WhatsApp, Discord, Slack, Teams) |
| `storage/` | SQLite (db.ts), workspace (memory.ts), pi-auth |

## API Routes

Routes live in `core/routes/*.ts`. Each exports a Hono router. Pattern:

- Use `getApiCtx(c)` and `getAuth(c)` for context
- Use `checkPerm(c, "permission.name")` for RBAC
- Return `c.json(...)` for responses

## Extensions

Extensions live in `.mercury/extensions/*/`. See [mercury-fork/docs/extensions.md](mercury-fork/docs/extensions.md) for the full API.

## Do Not Modify Without Understanding

- `resources/skills/` — Built-in pi agent skills (SKILL.md format). Changes affect mrctl commands inside containers.
